; Regression test for bug #1065: the C directive can create cycles in
; the smaller/larger commodity chains, causing infinite loops in
; in_place_reduce(), in_place_unreduce(), and value().
;
; The built-in conversions establish: 1h = 60m, 1m = 60s.
; Writing "C 3600s = 1h" creates a cycle: h -> m -> s -> h -> ...

C 3600s = 1h

2024/01/01 Test
    Expenses:Food    3600s
    Assets:Cash

test bal -> 1
__ERROR__
While parsing file "$FILE", line 8:
Error: Commodity conversion would create a cycle
end test
